gomodel:SYNGO_5175  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3a,b: Cultured hippocampal neurons were immunostained for endogenous Smaug1 (SAMD4A), PSD95 (DLG4) and synapsin. Smaug1 partially co-localized with PSD95 in closer proximity than presynaptic marker protein synapsin.\n\nFigure 3e: Smaug1 and PSD95 were enriched in PSD biochemical fractions from adult hippocampus as compared to input lysate and Synaptoneurosomes.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Hippocampal cultures were prepared as described previously (Banker and Goslin, 1998). In brief, hippocampi were dissected from Sprague Dawley rats at embryonic day 18 and digested with trypsin.\"\n\nantibody:\nanti-mammalian Smaug1, 1:300-1:1,000 (Baez and Boccaccio, 2005) PMID:16221671" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5175" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .
